AU  - Jordan, J. S.
T1  - Convergence to Rational Expectations in a Stationary Linear Game
PY  - 1992
Y1  - 1992/01/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297928
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 59
IS  - 1
SP  - 109
EP  - 123
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - This paper describes several learning processes which converge, with probability one, to the rational expectations (Bayesian-Nash) equilibrium of a stationary linear game. The learning processes include a test for convergence to equilibrium, and a method for changing the parameters of the process when non-convergence is indicated. This self-stabilization property eliminates the need to impose stability conditions on the economic environment. Convergence to equilibrium is proved for two types of self-stabilizing learning mechanisms: a centralized forecasting mechanism and a decentralized strategy adjustment process.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297928
ER  - 



