JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 59
IS  - 1
SP  - 125
EP  - 142
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - Profit rates differ across industries. Explanations have often relied on static models of imperfect competition. This paper develops a dynamic model of perfect competition to demonstrate that long-run average profit rates differ even across competitive industries when the effects of sunk costs on entry and exit are considered. The hypothesis that firms maximize their present expected values has few empirical implications for long-run average profit rates, but it does have implications for the behaviour of variables over time; for example, industries with high variability in the number of firms should exhibit low variability in firm values.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297929
ER  - 



